edu.rit.pj2.tuple

Class ObjectTuple<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.Tuple
      • edu.rit.pj2.tuple.ObjectTuple<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Content data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable, Cloneable

    public class ObjectTuple<T>
extends Tuple
    Class ObjectTuple provides a Tuple that contains a single object. The object must be streamable or serializable.

    • Method Detail

      • matchContent

        public boolean matchContent(Tuple target)
        Determine if the given target tuple's content matches this template's content. The target tuple is assumed to be an instance of this template's matching class or a subclass thereof.

        The ObjectTuple class's matchContent() method returns true if any of the following are true:

        • This template tuple's item field is null.
        • The target tuple's item field is null.
        • The target tuple's item is an instance of this template tuple's item's class or a subclass thereof.
        Overrides:
        matchContent in class Tuple
        Parameters:
        target - Target tuple.
        Returns:
        True if the target tuple's content matches this template tuple's content, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if target is null.
